    <briefdescription>
<para>Valid values for temperature and pressure IIR filter coefficient. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><formula id="1">\[
  data_n = \frac{data_{n-1} \times filtercoefficient + data_{in}}{filtercoefficient + 1}
\]</formula></para>
<para>where:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><formula id="2">$ data_n $</formula> is the current filtered output</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><formula id="3">$ data_{n-1} $</formula> is the previous filtered output</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><formula id="4">$ data_{in} $</formula> is the current input sample</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><formula id="5">$ filtercoefficient $</formula> is one of the coefficient values below</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Higher coefficient values provide more filtering (smoother output) but increase response time. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
